  ---

  ## Pricing Strategy

  ### Current Approach
  - **Hold prices constant** across all segments (control variable)
  - **Change framing/packaging** per segment (test variable)
  - **Measure conversion** by segment
  - If framing alone improves conversions â†’ pricing wasn't the issue
  - If specific segments struggle â†’ adjust price for THAT segment only

  ### Future Pricing Levers (per segment)

  | Segment | Potential Price Moves |
  |---------|----------------------|
  | BUSY_PRO | Premium for same-day/next-day, convenience fees |
  | PROP_MGR | Volume discounts, retainer model |
  | SMALL_BIZ | After-hours premium (25-50%), emergency premium |
  | BUDGET | Stripped-down basic tier, batching discounts |

  ---

  ## Add-Ons Roadmap (Future Innovation)

  | Segment | High-Converting Add-Ons |
  |---------|------------------------|
  | BUSY_PRO | "While I'm there" small fixes, photo documentation, extended guarantee |
  | PROP_MGR | Tenant coordination, bulk scheduling, preventive maintenance check |
  | SMALL_BIZ | After-hours upgrade, emergency priority line, quarterly maintenance retainer |
  | DIY_DEFERRER | Bundle discount for 3+ jobs, prepaid visit punch card |

  ---

